  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\"><img alt=\"Lys.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/50px-Lys.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/75px-Lys.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/100px-Lys.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Serenei of Lys</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\"><img alt=\"Lys.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/50px-Lys.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/75px-Lys.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/100px-Lys.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Serenei_of_Lys.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Serenei of Lys.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/89/Serenei_of_Lys.jpg/250px-Serenei_of_Lys.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"527\" srcset=\"/images/8/89/Serenei_of_Lys.jpg 1.5x\" /></a><div>Serenei, by Magali Villeneuve, as depicted in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nSweet Serenei<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\nLady<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Race</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyrian</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lyseni</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n~<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_126_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">126</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_172_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">172&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-ages_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ages-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_178_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">178</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/184_AC\" title=\"184 AC\">184&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-ages_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ages-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafshiera.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafshiera.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Lover</th><td>\nKing <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Shiera_Seastar\" title=\"Shiera Seastar\">Shiera Seastar</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Serenei of Lys</b>, also called <b>Sweet Serenei</b>, was the ninth and last mistress of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>. There was one child of their union, <a href=\"/index.php/Shiera_Seastar\" title=\"Shiera Seastar\">Shiera Seastar</a>, the last of the king's <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Bastards\" title=\"Great Bastards\">Great Bastards</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Serenei_of_Lys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dd><i>See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Serenei_of_Lys\" title=\"Category:Images of Serenei of Lys\">Images of Serenei of Lys</a></i></dd></dl>\n<p>Serenei was considered by many to be the most lovely of Aegon's mistresses.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\nShe was cold and haughty towards others at court.<sup id=\"cite_ref-SSM_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SSM-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sweet_Serenei_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e4/Sweet_Serenei_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/250px-Sweet_Serenei_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"354\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e4/Sweet_Serenei_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/375px-Sweet_Serenei_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e4/Sweet_Serenei_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/500px-Sweet_Serenei_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sweet_Serenei_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Serenei, by Jota Saraiva</div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Serenei_of_Lys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lady Serenei was the last daughter from an ancient but impoverished <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyrian</a> noble family of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>. She was brought to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Hightower\" title=\"Jon Hightower\">Jon Hightower</a>, the new <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>. Rumors spread that Serenei was much older than the king, practicing <a href=\"/index.php/Magic\" title=\"Magic\">dark arts</a> to retain her youth and beauty.<sup id=\"cite_ref-SSM_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SSM-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> She died giving birth to the last of the king’s bastard children, a girl called <a href=\"/index.php/Shiera_Seastar\" title=\"Shiera Seastar\">Shiera Seastar</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Serenei_of_Lys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ages-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-ages_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-ages_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>See the <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest/Calculations_Ages_(Continued3)#Serenei_of_Lys\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest/Calculations Ages (Continued3)\">Serenei of Lys</a> calculation.</i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafshiera.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafshiera.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Shiera.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-SSM-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-SSM_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-SSM_4-1\">4.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/Shiera_Seastar\">Shiera Seastar</a>, March 7, 2006</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403151546\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.127 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.388 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1059/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10837/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 11477/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 2711/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 12/40\nExpensive pars